Chubb: politicians and policy makers are not your peers (for the most part). Don't assume they know language & methods of science. #SciMPM
Chubb: consistency of effort and message is important. A spike in interest  from an op-ed is just a spike. Be passionate #SciMPM
Chubb: know your audience (they are busy) and that being an expert in your field doesn't make you and expert in everything #SciMPM
Chubb: if public don't come along with (and drive) a debate nothing will change #SciMPM
Chubb: if "science is good for you because science is good" days ever existed  they don't now. #SciMPM
Chubb: need to have two way respect  & trust between science & government for influence to be effective  #SciMPM
Chubb: relationships between scientists and governments vary around the world. Aust has had Chief Scientist since c.1983  #SciMPM
Chubb: enjoys his job  bringing experience to a position of influence #SciMPM
Chubb: need to distinguish means from ends. What's your end goal? How can we get there? #SciMPM
Schmidt: refer to experts before opening your mouth. Need to triangulate to ensure consistent messages to government #SciMPM
Schmidt: scientists need to be very careful to not mix scientific advice with advocating a policy response #SciMPM
Schmidt: leading scientists have an obligation to advocate consensus views of bodies like @Science_Academy #SciMPM
Schmidt: if you want to influence policy you need to decide if you will attach to one or other or neither side of politics. #SciMPM
Schmidt: best way to gain policy influence is to win a Nobel Prize (by a factor of x1 000 000) #SciMPM
Schmidt: two kinds of science in policy: 1. informing health  environment  defence policy 2. lobbying for science itself  #SciMPM
Now a panel with Ian Chubb  Veronica Taylor  Bruce Chapman and @cosmicpinot #SciMPM
Keating: science should have a seat at the good policy development table #SciMPM
Keating: economic policy intersects technology in areas like R&D tax breaks  and in defence research and acquisition #SciMPM
Keating: an important impact of technology is on economic growth & productivity. Also on improving health and longevity #SciMPM
Keating: some issues are very controversial inspite of no evidence of harmful consequences eg genetically modified foods #SciMPM
Keating: often not controversial  but exception is when impacts on people's property rights (eg water)  wealth  etc #SciMPM
Keating: technological advances in medicine  transport and agriculture drive policy development #SciMPM
Keating: science can influence policy making in some areas - eg health  industry  defence  environment  #SciMPM
Keating: policy making is an inexact science. Need to weigh evidence  cause & effect and judge responses ahead of time #SciMPM
